description: Beyoncé, Taylor Swift or Aya Nakamura's groupies don't mind waiting for hours on the sidewalk or spending a long time getting ready to try to look like the artists they admire. Photographer Clémentine Schneidermann captured them in pictures.
title: The world of fans according to Clémentine Schneidermann: 'I had no idea of the incredible phenomenon Aya Nakamura represents'

description: The tributes came in quickly in Italy on Sunday following the announcement of the death of the actor known for 'The Leopard,' 'L'Eclisse,' 'Rocco and His Brothers' and 'La prima notte di quiete,' all filmed with Italian directors.
title: Italy salutes Alain Delon as an actor who is also part of its history

description: The French superstar was thwarted by Mallorca goalkeeper Dominik Greif and after Rodrygo Goes sent Madrid ahead early on, the hosts leveled in the second half through Vedat Muriqi's towering header.
title: Mbappé and Madrid denied in Mallorca draw

description: A total of 600 firefighters, 11 water bombers and two helicopters have been deployed to contain the blaze in Frontignan, local civil security authorities said on X. Responders are struggling to predict the direction of the fire due to strong winds.
title: Wildfires engulf French town outside of Montpellier, with evacuations ongoing

description: The autonomous regions of the peninsula are reluctant to take in the 'menas' arriving in large numbers from Africa to the Canary Islands and immigration has now become a contentious issue.
title: Immigration: In Spain, the fate of unaccompanied minors fuels tensions

description: The Polish cyclist won her first women's Tour de France as she dug in during the race's grueling final Alpine ascent.
title: Niewiadoma wins Women's Tour de France by just four seconds

description: Japan is experiencing an exponential increase in tourism. The most popular sites are saturated, causing tensions with the local population. The government and regional authorities are seeking to diversify destinations but are having recruitment difficulties.
title: Overtourism: Japan tries to adapt but suffers from service worker shortage

description: In Latin America, a division between democracies and authoritarian regimes seems to have replaced the traditional left-right divide after Nicolas Maduro's self-proclaimed victory in the presidential election.
title: The left is being tested by the Venezuelan crisis

description: This French-Vietnamese woman fights for victims of the highly toxic herbicide. On August 22, the Paris Court of Appeal will rule on the liability of 14 American petrochemical giants for the millions of Agent Orange-caused deaths during the Vietnam War.
title: Tran To Nga's lifelong fight against Agent Orange

description: Between film shoots, the actor, who has died at age 88, visited museums and expanded his collections, which included paintings, sculptures and drawings.
title: Death of Alain Delon: 'Some people buy cars, but I prefer paintings'

description: Long neglected, the vineyards on the steep slopes of Sicily's volcano, the highest in Europe, have sparked a great deal of interest in recent years. Nearly 300 winemakers are making the most of the native grape varieties that flourish thanks to volcanic activity.
title: The eruption of Etna wines

description: According to OpenAI, its chatbot can now hold fluid spoken discussions and 'read' its users' emotions. The use of generative AI for therapeutic purposes is spreading, raising questions among healthcare professionals.
title: How AI is shaking up the mental health community: 'Rather than pay for another session, I'd go on ChatGPT'

description: As protests spread across the country, the opposition denounced the authorities's 'indulgence' of violence against women, forcing Prime Minister Narendra Modi to break his silence.
title: India: the rape and murder of a doctor shocks the country

description: To the dismay of many workers, venues dedicated to the Olympics including the Parc des Nations at La Villette were deserted by visitors, who totaled more than a million during the celebrations.
title: Calm, bored Paris hopes for returned fervor during the Paralympics

description: The Democratic National Convention, which opens in Chicago on August 19, will offer the vice president an opportunity to consolidate the momentum she has generated in record time since Joe Biden's withdrawal from the US presidential race.
title: Optimistic once again, the Democratic Party prepares to celebrate the advent of Kamala Harris

description: The French president said the film icon, who died aged 88, was not just a legendary actor but a 'monument.' Fellow 1960s star Brigitte Bardot said his death leaves 'a huge void.'
title: Death of Alain Delon: Macron and others pay tribute

description: During the Paris Olympic Games' closing ceremony, Tom Cruise was tasked with transferring the torch to California where several American stars, including Billie Eilish, were waiting on the beach.
title: Billie Eilish held a concert at the beach. Does anyone care?

description: Moscow has reportedly contacted Kyiv to initiate talks about a prisoner exchange. Eleven days after the start of its offensive on Russian territory, Ukraine continues to apply pressure on the Kremlin.
title: Ukrainian forces claim to hold many Russian soldiers captured in the Kursk region

description: Cop and thug, grace and violence, progressive acts and reactionary ideology, throughout his career and life, the actor, who died at the age of 88, walked a tightrope.
title: Alain Delon's death: The muted ambivalence of the man and the actor

description: The embodiment of the actor par excellence and a personality as much as an artist, Alain Delon lived his art with an unparalled intensity. He died at the age of 88.
title: Alain Delon, enduring star of French cinema, has died

description: US Secretary of State Antony Blinken flew out of Andrews Air Force Base after two days of ceasefire talks urged by President Joe Biden brokered with Egypt and Qatar wrapped up in the Qatari capital Doha. US officials said they made progress and offered a proposal to bridge gaps between Israel and Hamas.
title: Blinken heads back to Middle East as Gaza truce hopes rise

description: In 'Are We Dating the Same Guy?' Facebook groups, thousands of women share photos of lying, violent or manipulative men they've dealt with. From Paris to Los Angeles, these discussion forums recount the disappointments and fears associated with dating platforms.
title: 'Are We Dating the Same Guy?': Women support each other through dating app disappointments

description: 'The irresistible rise of Kamala Harris' (2/2). Elected San Francisco district attorney in 2003, the Democratic candidate for the White House showed her strength of character and commitment to defending the law in California.
title: Kamala Harris and the national destiny of an uncompromising prosecutor

description: At one point, criticizing a portrait of Harris on the cover of Time magazine, Trump insisted he was 'much better looking than her.' Republicans and Trump advisers – concerned by Harris's energized campaign – have publicly urged him to stick to the issues and lay off the personal attacks, but the former president has shown no sign of changing his populist, confrontational style.
title: Trump hurls fresh insults at 'lunatic' Harris as she gains popularity in the polls
